The draw for the 2020/2021 Champions League knockout stages have been conducted on Monday in Nyon, Switzerland. Defending champions Bayern Munich have been paired against Lazio, while Atletico Madrid plays Chelsea. Record winners Real Madrid will take on Atalanta, Liverpool have been drawn against RB Leipzig. Manchester City is to face Borussia Monchengladbach, as Barcelona clashes with Paris Saint-Germain. The Round of 16 matches will be played in February 2021. FULL FIXTURES Borussia Mochengladbach vs Manchester City Lazio vs Bayern Munich Atletico Madrid vs Chelsea RB Leipzig vs Liverpool Porto vs Juventus Barcelona vs PSG Sevilla vs Borussia Dortmund Atalanta vs Real Madrid